Docker Installation
  --------------------

2. sudo apt-get update
3. sudo apt-get install docker.io
4. To start docker---> sudo systemctl start docker
5. sudo systemctl status docker
6. sudo systemctl enable docker(Enable the Service for the boot time)
7. To install docker compose, run command: sudo apt install docker-compose
8. To run ngnix container---> sudo docker run -d -p 80:80 nginx
9: sudo docker ps


To Check Docker Version--> docker -v

**We are basically using docker to deploy springboot jar into an image.

** To build a docker image--->sudo docker build -f Dockerfile -t docker-spring-boot . : This will create a image file
with a new jar.

** To check docker images---> docker images

** To run the docker image---> docker run -p 8085:8085 docker-spring-boot
